GEICO is looking to fill thousands of positions at our regional offices across the country in order to remain available and ready to help our policyholders.

With the vast majority of GEICO\xe2\x80\x99s 41,000-associate population working from home due to COVID-19, all interviewing, hiring, onboarding and training will be done virtually. New associates will also work remotely until we transition back to our office locations. \xe2\x80\x9cWe are fortunate to be a stable company committed to serving our customers, developing associates and supporting our local communities,\xe2\x80\x9d said Todd Combs, President and CEO.

You can view all of our current open positions at geico.jobs.'

b'As part of our ongoing efforts to assist customers during this unprecedented time, GEICO is providing a 15% credit to auto and motorcycle customers as their policy comes up for renewal between April 8-October 7. Customers do not need to take any action to receive this credit. As previously announced, GEICO is pausing cancellations of coverage due to nonpayment and policy expiration through at least April 30, 2020. Beyond that, we remain committed to offering maximum flexibility to policyholders who need special payment options. We have also transitioned nearly all of our associates to work from home to continue providing the 24/7 service we are known for.'
